[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    Why not just use python in an interactive shell (or ipython) ? There are a few reasons:[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m       [0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m      - pyside does not yet allow Qt event processing and interactive shell at the same time[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m      - on some systems, typing in the console _blocks_ the qt event loop until the user presses ent[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m        be baffling and frustrating to users since it would appear the program has frozen.[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m      - some terminals (eg windows cmd.exe) have notoriously unfriendly interfaces[0m

[30;1m27 | [0m[35mAmongst the core features of pyqtgraph are:[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m* Basic data visualization primitives: Images, line and scatter plots[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m* Fast enough for realtime update of video/plot data[0m
